1
00:00:04,280 --> 00:00:06,120
Barbara?

2
00:00:10,440 --> 00:00:12,600
Sweet crib.

3
00:00:12,680 --> 00:00:15,400
You must be one rich cop.

4
00:00:15,480 --> 00:00:16,480
It's my girlfriend's place.

5
00:00:16,560 --> 00:00:17,840
Where is she?

6
00:00:17,920 --> 00:00:20,920
I don't know. Barbara?

7
00:00:23,920 --> 00:00:25,600
So... What?

8
00:00:25,680 --> 00:00:26,920
I get to stay here alone?

9
00:00:30,200 --> 00:00:31,200
I'm hungry.

10
00:00:32,600 --> 00:00:36,400
<i>Dear Jim, I thought I could be strong
and brave for you, but I can't.</i>

11
00:00:36,480 --> 00:00:40,680
<i>Every place I go,
I see Falcone and Zsasz.</i>

12
00:00:40,760 --> 00:00:42,320
<i>I'm nervous and needy and screwed up</i>

13
00:00:42,400 --> 00:00:44,560
<i>and I know that's not
what you need or want,</i>

14
00:00:44,640 --> 00:00:47,520
<i>so I'm going away for a while,
to get myself together.</i>

15
00:00:52,800 --> 00:00:53,960
This is Gordon.

16
00:00:56,400 --> 00:00:57,400
Right. Yeah.

17
00:00:57,480 --> 00:00:59,840
We're in the penthouse. Come on up.

18
00:01:05,360 --> 00:01:07,800
Sounds like your girlfriend's
not coming back, huh?

19
00:01:09,200 --> 00:01:10,720
Why's she worried about Falcone?

20
00:01:10,800 --> 00:01:12,120
None of your business.

21
00:01:13,280 --> 00:01:14,600
So, what happens now?

22
00:01:14,680 --> 00:01:16,360
You gonna get the charges
against me dropped?

23
00:01:16,440 --> 00:01:18,800
I will, but you're my only witness
to the Wayne murders.

24
00:01:18,880 --> 00:01:20,960
You gonna cuff me
to a drainpipe again?

25
00:01:21,040 --> 00:01:22,640
No, I'm not gonna hold you
against your will.

26
00:01:22,720 --> 00:01:24,640
GCPD, juvie, you'd just break out.

27
00:01:24,720 --> 00:01:26,600
So I do get to stay here.

28
00:01:26,680 --> 00:01:28,600
No, I have someplace else in mind.

29
00:01:30,840 --> 00:01:32,280
That's the sketch artist.

30
00:01:32,360 --> 00:01:34,320
I need you to describe
the man who shot the Waynes.

31
00:01:35,800 --> 00:01:39,200
- Wait, where am I going to stay?
- Wayne manor.

32
00:01:48,520 --> 00:01:50,040
Do not speak to the inmate.

33
00:01:50,120 --> 00:01:52,240
Do not touch the inmate unless
in the service of your job.

34
00:01:52,320 --> 00:01:55,280
Do not accept anything from
the inmate under any circumstances.

35
00:01:55,360 --> 00:01:56,640
Who is this guy, anyway?

36
00:01:56,720 --> 00:01:59,240
Name's Ian Hargrove,
some genius bomb maker.

37
00:01:59,320 --> 00:02:01,520
Took out over a dozen buildings
in and around Gotham.

38
00:02:01,600 --> 00:02:03,080
He's the one that blew up
the commissary last month?

39
00:02:03,160 --> 00:02:05,320
Yeah, and he did it
with match shavings

40
00:02:05,400 --> 00:02:06,480
and apple cider vinegar.

41
00:02:06,560 --> 00:02:08,320
So no mistakes today, got it?

42
00:02:25,480 --> 00:02:27,320
Put your hands up.

43
00:02:42,640 --> 00:02:45,760
She said this is the man
who killed your parents.

44
00:02:45,840 --> 00:02:48,520
She said she saw his face.

45
00:02:48,600 --> 00:02:50,360
Do you recognize him, Bruce?

46
00:02:51,440 --> 00:02:52,800
No.

47
00:02:55,360 --> 00:02:58,120
- What's her name?
- Selina Kyle.

48
00:02:58,200 --> 00:02:59,720
Do you believe her?

49
00:02:59,800 --> 00:03:01,840
Yes, I do.

50
00:03:01,920 --> 00:03:03,920
So, she saw...

51
00:03:04,000 --> 00:03:05,000
Everything?

52
00:03:06,800 --> 00:03:09,360
And you want her to live here
with us, do you?

53
00:03:10,720 --> 00:03:12,080
A common street criminal.

54
00:03:12,160 --> 00:03:13,440
She's hardly older than Bruce.

55
00:03:13,520 --> 00:03:16,200
She's just a kid who's seen too much.

56
00:03:16,280 --> 00:03:18,440
This is for her safety.

57
00:03:18,520 --> 00:03:19,760
GCPD is full of moles...

58
00:03:19,840 --> 00:03:22,040
Right, and how long
would you have us put her up, then?

59
00:03:22,120 --> 00:03:23,480
I don't know.

60
00:03:24,720 --> 00:03:25,720
No. The answer is no.

61
00:03:25,800 --> 00:03:28,480
Her being here will put Master Bruce
in great danger.

62
00:03:28,560 --> 00:03:29,720
Alfred.

63
00:03:29,800 --> 00:03:32,680
She is the witness
to a murder, Master Bruce.

64
00:03:32,760 --> 00:03:34,000
You do understand that, don't you?

65
00:03:34,080 --> 00:03:36,720
She's also the best chance we have
of finding who killed my parents.

66
00:03:37,760 --> 00:03:39,080
Isn't she?

67
00:03:39,160 --> 00:03:40,240
Yes, she is.

68
00:03:41,840 --> 00:03:42,840
Then she can stay.

69
00:03:44,640 --> 00:03:46,240
As long as it takes.

70
00:03:50,040 --> 00:03:51,720
I've made my decision.

71
00:03:54,240 --> 00:03:55,400
Yes, Master Bruce.

72
00:03:58,160 --> 00:04:01,120
Look, I know this is a lot.

73
00:04:01,200 --> 00:04:03,120
But I'm doing everything I can.

74
00:04:03,200 --> 00:04:05,360
Montoya and Allen and I
are meeting with an ADA

75
00:04:05,440 --> 00:04:06,720
they trust this afternoon.

76
00:04:08,760 --> 00:04:10,280
A trustworthy lawyer.

77
00:04:11,480 --> 00:04:12,480
In Gotham.

78
00:04:12,560 --> 00:04:15,440
Look, if we find this guy,
we'll need her.

79
00:04:16,520 --> 00:04:17,680
She'll have to testify.

80
00:04:17,760 --> 00:04:20,440
Go before a judge. It won't be easy.

81
00:04:20,520 --> 00:04:22,160
Witnesses back out all the time.

82
00:04:22,240 --> 00:04:26,080
The ones that stick it out do so
because they care about the victims.

83
00:04:26,160 --> 00:04:28,960
We'll do our best to be nice to her,
then, won't we?

84
