It's from the Chinese Ming Dynasty.

85
00:04:45,040 --> 00:04:46,040
Five...

86
00:04:50,240 --> 00:04:52,400
Five hundred years old.

87
00:04:52,480 --> 00:04:55,600
You can get one just like it
for five bucks, in Chinatown.

88
00:05:05,040 --> 00:05:06,080
I'm Bruce Wayne.

89
00:05:10,160 --> 00:05:11,640
Selina Kyle.

90
00:05:13,400 --> 00:05:14,800
People call me Cat.

91
00:05:16,680 --> 00:05:18,000
Nice to meet you, Cat.

92
00:05:28,480 --> 00:05:29,600
What are you doing?

93
00:05:31,280 --> 00:05:32,440
Nothing.

94
00:05:32,520 --> 00:05:33,560
What's in your hand?

95
00:05:34,640 --> 00:05:35,640
I said, what's in...

96
00:05:47,520 --> 00:05:48,880
What the hell...

97
00:06:15,960 --> 00:06:17,480
Hargrove!

98
00:06:19,360 --> 00:06:22,520
Ian Hargrove, time to go.

99
00:06:30,400 --> 00:06:32,600
Kid, you screwed up, big-time.

100
00:06:32,680 --> 00:06:35,480
{\an5}But you're still young,
you deserve a second chance.

101
00:06:35,560 --> 00:06:36,920
So I have a bet for you.

102
00:06:38,200 --> 00:06:40,400
{\an5}You call heads or tails.

103
00:06:40,480 --> 00:06:42,600
{\an5}You lose, you go to jail.

104
00:06:43,640 --> 00:06:44,880
You win, we let you go.

105
00:06:44,960 --> 00:06:47,600
{\an5}- Bet.
- Hold on.

106
00:06:47,680 --> 00:06:49,640
{\an5}There's a catch.

107
00:06:49,720 --> 00:06:51,400
You have to make a promise
to God right now.

108
00:06:51,480 --> 00:06:53,600
{\an5}If you win, you're gonna
take this as a sign from him

109
00:06:53,680 --> 00:06:55,240
{\an5}telling you that you need
to go back to school

110
00:06:55,320 --> 00:06:57,160
{\an5}and get your life straight.

111
00:06:57,240 --> 00:06:58,560
Can you promise that?

112
00:06:58,640 --> 00:07:00,000
Do you promise that?

113
00:07:01,040 --> 00:07:02,440
Yes, sir.

114
00:07:04,080 --> 00:07:05,320
Okay, then.

115
00:07:07,960 --> 00:07:09,840
- Call.
- Heads.

116
00:07:14,000 --> 00:07:15,400
Walk away, kid.

117
00:07:16,880 --> 00:07:17,920
Somebody up there loves you.

118
00:07:18,000 --> 00:07:19,800
Hey, Harvey.

119
00:07:22,600 --> 00:07:24,560
{\an5}Go. Remember your promise.

120
00:07:26,240 --> 00:07:27,640
{\an5}Jim Gordon, GCPD.

121
00:07:27,720 --> 00:07:29,200
{\an5}I hear good things
about you, counselor.

122
00:07:29,280 --> 00:07:31,520
{\an5}Harvey Dent, likewise
about you, detective.

123
00:07:31,600 --> 00:07:33,520
That was some trick with the coin.

124
00:07:33,600 --> 00:07:35,000
What if the kid guesses wrong?

125
00:07:35,080 --> 00:07:36,280
You gonna send him to jail?

126
00:07:36,360 --> 00:07:37,960
{\an5}Teenagers,
they nearly always call heads.

127
00:07:38,040 --> 00:07:39,240
{\an5}I don't know why.

128
00:07:41,280 --> 00:07:43,000
Two-headed coin.

129
00:07:44,000 --> 00:07:45,680
Whatever works, right?

130
00:07:45,760 --> 00:07:47,560
So who is he, Jim?

131
00:07:47,640 --> 00:07:49,000
Who really killed the Waynes?

132
00:07:49,080 --> 00:07:50,840
{\an5}Well, this is what we have.

133
00:07:52,280 --> 00:07:53,800
{\an5}No ID.

134
00:07:53,880 --> 00:07:55,520
{\an5}But this is from an eyewitness?

135
00:07:55,600 --> 00:07:56,760
{\an5}That you have in safe custody.

136
00:07:58,000 --> 00:08:00,280
{\an5}It's not nearly enough
to go to the law with.

137
00:08:00,360 --> 00:08:01,760
{\an5}Even if we had ID on this guy,

138
00:08:01,840 --> 00:08:03,280
{\an5}it's the people who hired him
we really want.

139
00:08:03,360 --> 00:08:04,600
{\an5}I agree.

140
00:08:04,680 --> 00:08:06,520
{\an5}Your eyewitness is useless
in a courtroom.

141
00:08:06,600 --> 00:08:11,080
{\an5}But the idea of your witness
could be immensely valuable.

142
00:08:13,680 --> 00:08:15,240
Ever hear the name, Dick Lovecraft?

143
00:08:15,320 --> 00:08:17,160
{\an5}Sure. Billionaire.

144
00:08:17,240 --> 00:08:19,120
{\an5}Property, construction, chemicals.

145
00:08:19,200 --> 00:08:20,960
{\an5}And as corrupt as they come.

146
00:08:21,040 --> 00:08:24,520
{\an5}Falcone, Maroni,
even Wayne enterprises,

147
00:08:24,600 --> 00:08:26,200
Lovecraft has dealings
with all of them.

148
00:08:26,280 --> 00:08:28,320
Since the Waynes' deaths,
he's doubled his fortune.

149
00:08:28,400 --> 00:08:30,200
Including a huge piece
of the Arkham deal.

150
00:08:30,280 --> 00:08:32,720
{\an5}Lovecraft had a long feud
with Thomas Wayne

151
00:08:32,800 --> 00:08:34,200
{\an5}over deals and politics.

152
00:08:34,280 --> 00:08:36,360
They couldn't have had a more
different vision for Gotham.

153
00:08:36,440 --> 00:08:38,080
I'm willing to bet my career

154
00:08:38,160 --> 00:08:39,640
on his involvement
in the Wayne murders.

155
00:08:39,720 --> 00:08:40,800
That's a big bet.

156
00:08:40,880 --> 00:08:43,520
I want to use your witness
To go after Lovecraft.

157
00:08:43,600 --> 00:08:47,440
{\an5}How? My witness can't connect
Lovecraft to the perp.

158
00:08:47,520 --> 00:08:49,680
{\an5}Lovecraft doesn't know that.

159
00:08:49,760 --> 00:08:51,440
I'll let it leak out.

160
00:08:51,520 --> 00:08:53,040
{\an5}That we have a secret eyewitness

161
00:08:53,120 --> 00:08:54,920
{\an5}who's going to blow
the case wide open

162
00:08:55,000 --> 00:08:57,160
{\an5}and connect Lovecraft
to the Wayne killings.

163
00:08:57,240 --> 00:08:59,000
Lovecraft will get very nervous.

164
00:08:59,080 --> 00:09:01,040
And the people around him
will get nervous.

165
00:09:01,120 --> 00:09:03,520
{\an5}And that's when people start talking,
you know how that goes.

166
00:09:03,600 --> 00:09:05,760
{\an5}Unless Lovecraft wasn't involved
in the Wayne murders.

167
00:09:05,840 --> 00:09:08,160
If so, which I doubt, we still win.

168
00:09:08,240 --> 00:09:10,040
Whoever was involved
in the Wayne killings

169
00:09:10,120 --> 00:09:11,840
will get their cage rattled
like the dickens, won't they?

170
00:09:11,920 --> 00:09:14,600
- I bet he makes a move.
- You like to bet a lot.

171
00:09:15,840 --> 00:09:16,880
{\an5}Well, what do we got to lose?

172
00:09:16,960 --> 00:09:18,320
My witness becomes a target.

173
00:09:18,400 --> 00:09:20,160
{\an5}No. That's the beauty of it.

174
00:09:20,240 --> 00:09:21,480
{\an5}We never actually file papers.

175
00:09:21,560 --> 00:09:23,680
{\an5}We never name names.

176
00:09:23,760 --> 00:09:25,360
{\an5}It's just a powerful story.

177
00:09:25,440 --> 00:09:27,240
Your witness is perfectly safe.

178
00:09:27,320 --> 00:09:28,640
And you're on board with this?

179
00:09:28,720 --> 00:09:29,920
We've been on board, Jim.

180
00:09:30,000 --> 00:09:31,960
Harvey's one of us.

181
00:09:32,040 --> 00:09:33,360
I want what you want, Jim.

182
00:09:34,920 --> 00:09:36,960
{\an5}I want to make this city
a better place.

183
00:09:41,160 --> 00:09:42,560
No names.

184
00:09:42,640 --> 00:09:46,520
Not mine, not my witness,
nothing, just a story.

185
00:09:46,600 --> 00:09:48,400
Just a story.

186
00:09:49,520 --> 00:09:50,800
All right.

187
00:09:50,880 --> 00:09:51,920
Let's try something.

188
00:09:57,520 --> 00:09:59,600
Hey, I thought I was gonna have
to work this case without you.

189
00:09:59,680 --> 00:10:01,400
Where the hell have you been?
You know what?

190
00:10:01,480 --> 00:10:04,080
On second thought, never mind,
I don't want to know.

191
00:10:04,160 --> 00:10:06,400
- What do we got?
- A biggie.

192
00:10:06,480 --> 00:10:07,560
Blackgate prisoner escaped

193
00:10:07,640 --> 00:10:09,920
while in transit to St. Mark's
for psychiatric care.

194
00:10:10,000 --> 00:10:12,480
His name's Ian Hargrove,
clinically insane,

195
00:10:12,560 --> 00:10:14,720
with a compulsion
for blowing things up.

196
00:10:14,800 --> 00:10:16,840
He exploded a bunch
of old buildings around Gotham.

197
00:10:16,920 --> 00:10:19,360
Last one, two janitors were killed.

198
00:10:19,440 --> 00:10:21,480
Says here he was busted out
by four gunmen?

199
00:10:21,560 --> 00:10:25,320
Yeah, which is odd,
Hargrove never used accomplices.

200
00:10:25,400 --> 00:10:27,800
All right, so who did Hargrove
spend time with at Blackgate?

201
00:10:27,880 --> 00:10:29,320
Who did he communicate
with on the outside?

202
00:10:29,400 --> 00:10:33,000
His entire stretch,
he was isolated from gen pop.

203
00:10:33,080 --> 00:10:34,440
Never made or received phone calls.

204
00:10:34,520 --> 00:10:37,880
Only one visitor in those two years,
his brother John.

205
00:10:37,960 --> 00:10:39,880
- Got an address?
- We do.

206
00:10:39,960 --> 00:10:41,960
Unis are bringing him
in right now for questioning.

207
00:10:42,040 --> 00:10:44,360
We're lucky you deigned to show up.

208
00:10:44,440 --> 00:10:45,800
Yeah, sorry.

209
00:10:45,880 --> 00:10:47,720
No problem.

210
00:10:49,800 --> 00:10:53,360
- Girl trouble?
- Yeah.

211
00:10:53,440 --> 00:10:57,360
I told you. Those high society dames,
get you all twisted.

212
00:11:00,840 --> 00:11:02,720
Keep your guard up.
Knock lumps out of you.

213
00:11:02,800 --> 00:11:03,960
Watch your feet.

214
00:11:04,040 --> 00:11:05,400
Right. Jab, jab, right.

215
00:11:06,720 --> 00:11:08,160
- Lead with the...
- Hey!

216
00:11:08,240 --> 00:11:09,680
Jab, jab, right.

217
00:11:09,760 --> 00:11:11,480
Keep that guard up, jab, jab, right.

218
00:11:11,560 --> 00:11:13,960
Lead, Jab, jab, right.

219
00:11:14,040 --> 00:11:15,400
Jab, jab, right.

220
00:11:15,480 --> 00:11:16,840
Now keep that...

221
00:11:17,840 --> 00:11:19,160
Yes.

222
00:11:20,240 --> 00:11:21,400
Sorry, Alfred.

223
00:11:21,480 --> 00:11:22,560
- Hello.
- Bruce.

224
00:11:26,280 --> 00:11:27,920
- That hurt.
- Yeah, it's supposed to, isn't it?

225
00:11:28,000 --> 00:11:32,320
Taking a punch is just as important
as throwing one, Master Bruce.

226
00:11:32,400 --> 00:11:34,880
- What you doing?
- Alfred's teaching me to fight.

227
00:11:34,960 --> 00:11:36,120
Why?

228
00:11:37,280 --> 00:11:39,480
So I'll be prepared
if something bad happens.

229
00:11:39,560 --> 00:11:43,200
Yeah, 'cause you live
in a pretty rough neighborhood.

230
00:11:43,280 --> 00:11:45,560
Not here, in Gotham.

231
00:11:45,640 --> 00:11:47,520
In Gotham, people don't fight
with gloves on.

232
00:11:51,360 --> 00:11:52,600
How's your room? Everything good?

233
00:11:54,640 --> 00:11:57,280
It'll do. I'm hungry, though.

234
00:11:57,360 --> 00:12:01,160
Right. Well, breakfast
was served at 8.00, miss,

235
00:12:01,240 --> 00:12:02,720
which you slept through.

236
00:12:04,000 --> 00:12:05,080
Lunch shall be served at 12.00.

237
00:12:05,160 --> 00:12:06,920
There's plenty to eat in the kitchen
and Alfred will be happy

238
00:12:07,000 --> 00:12:08,280
- to fix you something.
- No, he won't be, will he?

239
00:12:08,360 --> 00:12:10,080
Because it's not a bloody hotel.

240
00:12:12,520 --> 00:12:15,200
Relax, old man. I'll figure it out.

241
00:12:15,280 --> 00:12:16,560
Yeah, you can mind
your manners as well,

242
00:12:16,640 --> 00:12:18,280
you cheeky little minx.

243
00:12:18,360 --> 00:12:20,520
Be nice to her, Alfred,
she's our guest.

244
00:12:20,600 --> 00:12:22,920
Well, I'm terribly sorry,
Master Bruce.

245
00:12:24,200 --> 00:12:26,120
Didn't realize you fancied her.

246
00:12:26,200 --> 00:12:28,320
What do you mean? No.

247
00:12:28,400 --> 00:12:29,840
Well, it's nothing
to be embarrassed about.

248
00:12:29,920 --> 00:12:31,160
It's only natural, isn't it?

249
00:12:31,240 --> 00:12:33,000
But you watch her.

250
00:12:34,240 --> 00:12:36,040
She's a lairy one.

251
00:12:36,120 --> 00:12:38,760
Right. Left, left, right.

252
00:12:38,840 --> 00:12:41,400
keep your guard up, son.

253
00:12:41,480 --> 00:12:43,400
You know about girls, do you, Alfred?

254
00:12:43,480 --> 00:12:45,600
Fair sight more than you.

255
00:12:45,680 --> 00:12:49,200
And she, mate, is trouble watch.

